results.title: Bad dogs have more fun [electronic resource] : Selected Writings on Family, Animals, and Life from The Philadelphia Inquirer. John Grogan.
abstracts: Bad Dogs Have More Fun is an unforgettable collection of more than 75 newspaper columns by John Grogan, the number-one New York Times best-selling author of Marley & Me. Combining humor, wit, poignancy and affection, these columns provide insight into the intriguing and wonderful world we live in. Whether it be writing about animals (from dogs to elephants to geese!), his powerful and moving comments about his own and other families, his trenchant comments on life's foibles and farces, or his interviews and interactions with people who are memorable and unusual in their own right, John Grogan makes us laugh, he makes us cry, he makes us think.

results.title: Contrary to popular opinion [electronic resource]. Alan M Dershowitz.
abstracts: Dershowitz selects his most recent newspaper columns, articles and essays and adds original commentary to present an engaging and spirited discussion about many of today's most controversial issues.

results.title: Devil in dover [electronic resource] : An Insider’s Story of Dogma v. Darwin in Small-Town America. Lauri Lebo.
abstracts: The page-turning first-person story behind the 2005 intelligent design case in Dover, Pennsylvania.

results.title: Speak after the beep [electronic resource]. Michael Frayn.
abstracts: Jarvis and Frayn are a truly inimitable pairing - frequent collaborators on-stage, screen and audiobook, they are an eternally popular duo. Michael Frayn began his career as a reporter on UK newspaper The Guardian before becoming a columnist for the same newspaper. Martin Jarvis is a renowned audiobook narrator and his many acting accolades include winning a Theater World Award for his performance in Braodway play 'By Jeeves' This collection is perfect for anyone who has ever questioned the logic behind technobabble, computer jargon and eccentric human idiosyncrasies...that'll be everybody, then!.

results.title: Desperate glory [electronic resource]. Sam Kiley.
abstracts: In the dust and blazing heat of Helmand, the young men of 16 Air Assault Brigade find themselves in the most relentless battles faced by British troops in recent history. As the only writer to have unrestricted access to the front line, Sam Kiley is there to bear witness to the most intense challenges of their lives. Desperate Glory is an unflinching portrait of the reality of war.
